    <values>
        <field>Description__c</field>
        <value xsi:type="xsd:string">A guest profile has PermissionsApiEnabled=true. This allows unauthenticated callers to reach the Salesforce REST and SOAP API without any credentials.</value>
    </values>
    <values>
        <field>Impact__c</field>
        <value xsi:type="xsd:string">Anonymous API access allows credential-free automation against your Salesforce org from any IP address globally. Attackers can perform bulk data extraction, record creation, or deletion without authenticating.</value>
    </values>
    <values>
        <field>Remediation__c</field>
        <value xsi:type="xsd:string">Remove API Enabled from all guest profiles. API integrations must use named credentials with a dedicated integration user. There is no valid use case for unauthenticated API access.</value>
    </values>
